Adjust rack to middle position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and peel @carrots{12%ounce}; halve lengthwise and cut crosswise on a diagonal into ½-inch pieces. Strip @thyme{¼%ounce} leaves from stems; finely chop leaves until you have 2 tsp (4 tsp for 4 servings). Halve, peel, and finely dice half the @yellow onion{1}; thinly slice remaining half. Zest and quarter @lemon{1}.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}, @honey{4%teaspoon}, ¼ tsp chopped thyme (½ tsp for 4 servings), @salt{}, and @pepper{}. (You'll use more thyme later.)

Roast until browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Melt @butter{2%tablespoon} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add diced onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until translucent, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add @Israeli couscous{½%cup}; cook, stirring, until lightly toasted, ~{10-20%seconds}.

Add half the @chicken stock concentrate{2%unit}, @water{¾%cup} (1 1/2 cups for 4) and a big pinch of salt. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until couscous is tender, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Drain any excess water if necessary. Stir in a pinch of lemon zest. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Pat @pork chops{10%ounce} dry with paper towels. Place in a #medium bowl{}; season all over with @Fry seasoning{1%tablespoon}, half the @flour{1%tablespoon} (you'll use the rest in the next step), ½ tsp chopped thyme (¾ tsp for 4 servings), salt, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest. Wipe out pan.

Melt 1 TBSP butter (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in same pan over medium heat. Add sliced onion and cook, stirring, until softened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add a drizzle of oil, remaining flour, and ¼ tsp chopped thyme (½ tsp for 4); cook, stirring, until lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Whisk in @water{1%cup} (2 cups for 4), @beef stock concentrate{1%unit}, remaining chicken stock concentrates, and juice from one lemon wedge (two wedges for 4). Bring to a simmer and cook, whisking constantly, until thickened, ~{3-5%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Slice pork crosswise.

Divide couscous and carrots between plates. Top couscous with pork and as much gravy as you like. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.